Blargh. I'm so disappointed in this location- Dunkin Donuts has really been letting me down in general, lately. They really need to set a higher standard for their franchises. This location is situated is such a convenient spot, and it's pretty nice, aesthetically speaking, however I just don't know if I can stomach ever coming here again. I came in to order just a few days ago. There was only one person that appeared to be working. I was really looking forward to coming here, since it was on my way to work, and I was actually allowing myself to have some of the things here that I normally wouldn't order, for health reasons. I already started ordering. Not only did the employee seem somewhat incompetent, and I could barely understand his speech, but then...  ... ..he.....picked his nose. Right in front of me! While he was taking my order! Gross!!! I was kind of stunned as I stumbled through my words to cancel my order, and high tailed it out of there!

I come into this Dunkin' at all different times a day, different days of the week because I live across the street. I always get a "refill" of coffee (which is at a discount price) in my Contigo coffee cup because it keeps my coffee hot other than the many Dunkin' donuts mugs I have at home. Today they told me they charge regular price for coffee in a non coffee cup. I have even had the manager take my cup to refill plenty of times before and I spoke with him and he was very nice and just explained to me that it's their policy. Which I understand. Working in the service industry though and being a manager I would accommodate my regulars. The casier was incredibly rude about this also. I will be going to the Dunkin' on lake atreet from now on.
